  "body": "Ref: NCC-EF-Clef-003 \r\n\r\nAn attacker with permissions to the encrypted backup files of Clef could swap around the\r\nencrypted passwords for the user’s keystores. This could allow weak attacks like confirming\r\nif different keys are protected by the same passphrase, or more complex attacks depending\r\non the rules in use by Clef.\r\n\r\nRecommendation: Include the key-value’s key in the additionalData field of the Seal() and Open() functions.\r\nSee the cipher [package](https://golang.org/pkg/crypto/cipher/) for more information. \r\n\r\n---\r\nNote: this requires rw-access to the filesystem, so the attack is mostly moot in the current threat model. It's totally unnecessary to have it like this, however, when it's so easy to fix. ",
